\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3.1}{\ignorespaces The four possible slot states in an Aleph Filter. The unary code is self-delimiting: read 1s until a 0 is encountered, then the remaining bits are the fingerprint. A void entry has no fingerprint; a tombstone is distinguished by an all-1s pattern.}}{24}{figure.caption.34}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:slot-format}{{3.1}{24}{The four possible slot states in an Aleph Filter. The unary code is self-delimiting: read 1s until a 0 is encountered, then the remaining bits are the fingerprint. A void entry has no fingerprint; a tombstone is distinguished by an all-1s pattern}{figure.caption.34}{}}
